comments: During Williamson's (NOP) natural upward shooting motion, he makes marginal contact with Wade's (CLE) face. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Adams (NOP) slides his arm across Wade's (CLE) front and makes marginal contact with Wade during the screen.
Wade (CLE) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Adams' (NOP) path.
Adams (NOP) legally contests Love's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
Okoro (CLE) makes marginal contact with Ingram (NOP) as he secures the rebound.
As Williamson (NOP) lowers his upper body and turns toward the basket, Okoro (CLE) makes marginal contact with Williamson at the end of the drive.
Bledsoe (NOP) legally contests Dellavedova's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
Osman (CLE) legally contests Bledsoe's (NOP) jump shot attempt.
Johnson (NOP) makes contact with Osman's (CLE) arm.
Ingram (NOP) legally contests Love's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
Wade (CLE) places a hand on Williamson's (NOP) back but does not extend or deliver contact as he makes contact with the ball during the steal.
As Dellavedova (CLE) is securing the loose ball, Williamson (NOP) moves toward him and marginal contact occurs when Dellavedova makes the pass.
Osman (CLE) commits a take foul on Bledsoe (NOP).
Lewis Jr. (NOP) legally contests Wade's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
Stevens (CLE) commits a take foul on Ingram (NOP).
Johnson (NOP) legally contests Wade's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
